# AeroCraft Portal Code Style

## Component Rules
- One component per `.tsx` file — no exceptions (exception: small icon registries such as `*.icons.tsx` that only export constants).
- Avoid React `style={{}}` on Bear primitives and layout; prefer classes in `src/styles/index.css` with the `ac-` prefix. Narrow exceptions: dynamic iframe `minHeight` / `opacity`, and tooltip coordinates tied to pointer position.
- No magic numbers in TS/TSX — use `@const/numbers.const.ts` (or feature-specific const files when justified).
- No raw string literals for repeated symbols — use `@const/strings.const.ts` (`EMPTY_STRING`, shared hex labels, aria strings, etc.). User-visible copy belongs in `@i18n/*`, not hardcoded in components.
- No hardcoded UI sentences — all user-facing text through `useI18n()` / `Messages`.

## File Responsibilities
- `*.types.ts` — interfaces and type aliases only
- `*.const.ts` — constants, numbers, strings (no JSX)
- `*.tsx` — single React component (or icon registry export only)

## Imports
- `import type` for all type-only imports
- Path aliases: `@/*`, `@types/*`, `@const/*`, `@i18n/*`, `@pages/*`, `@components/*`, `@utils/*`, `@data/*`, `@config/*`
- No `../../` (or deeper) relative paths when an alias is available; same-folder `../Sibling` is fine

## Shared theme colors
- Default pink/red/yellow/blue scales ship in `@forgedevstack/aerocraft` (`DEFAULT_THEME_COLORS`). The portal imports scales through `@const/extendedThemeColors.const.ts`, which re-exports from the package. Project-specific tokens live in `aerocraft.config.js` under `theme.colors`.

## Tooling
- **Vite path aliases:** `vite-tsconfig-paths` reads `tsconfig.json` `paths`. Keep an explicit `resolve.alias` entry for `@config` → `src/config` in `vite.config.ts` so imports like `@config/portal.config` always resolve (some setups do not expand `@config/*` reliably).
- Other special cases: `vue` stub path in `vite.config.ts`.
- **VS Code extension (`aero-craft-plugin` / `aerocraft-bear-forgestack`):** open that repo, run `npm install` (build runs via `postinstall`), reload the window, then `npx vsce package` and install the `.vsix` via **Extensions → Install from VSIX…**, or **F5** for the extension development host. The extension suggests AeroCraft classes in `class` / `className` and Bear snippets when `aerocraft.config.*` is present in the workspace.

## Bear Components Only
- Use Bear for all UI: `Card`, `Typography`, `Button`, `Flex`, `Badge`, `Divider`, `Input`, `Tabs`, `AppBar`, `Sidebar`, `Dropdown`, `Chip`, `Alert`, `Spinner`
- Colors via `BearProvider` theme — never hardcode color values inline for marketing surfaces; use CSS classes or theme tokens
- No raw `<div>` for layout — use `<Flex>` or `<Card>`
